1
00:00:02,168 --> 00:00:06,005
We are kicking off this evening

2
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:10,210
a week-long celebration
of a landmark event,

3
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:11,878
which is the golden anniversary

4
00:00:11,878 --> 00:00:15,815
of the Allerton Conference on Communication, Control,

5
00:00:15,815 --> 00:00:17,784
and Computing.

6
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:21,187
For those of you who have
been regular attendees

7
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:24,124
at the Allerton Conference
for many years

8
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:29,162
and for some probably Allerton is special place

9
00:00:29,162 --> 00:00:30,797
in your career,

10
00:00:30,797 --> 00:00:33,032
having presented
your first paper

11
00:00:33,032 --> 00:00:36,736
or second paper in your career at the Allerton Conference,

12
00:00:36,736 --> 00:00:40,740
and I know that there are
many of you out there.

13
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:44,744
For those of you for whom this
is the very first

14
00:00:44,744 --> 00:00:46,880
Allerton Conference,

15
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:51,151
an-and for all conference attendees and for our guests,

16
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:53,920
this is a historic moment.

17
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:54,988
It's a celebration

18
00:00:54,988 --> 00:00:59,092
of a multi-disciplinary scientific meeting

19
00:00:59,092 --> 00:01:06,065
which was launched 50 years ago on November 15, 1963

20
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:11,438
with vision and
incredible foresight.

21
00:01:11,438 --> 00:01:15,341
It was the brainchild
of Mac Van Valkenburg

22
00:01:15,341 --> 00:01:17,944
who, together with Joe Cruz,

23
00:01:17,944 --> 00:01:23,183
co-chaired the first conference 50 years ago.

24
00:01:23,183 --> 00:01:26,519
Bill Perkins, eh, who is here,

25
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:29,189
ehht, and, eh,

26
00:01:29,189 --> 00:01:32,959
he was also involved
in the initial discussions

27
00:01:32,959 --> 00:01:35,161
and planning of the conference,

28
00:01:35,161 --> 00:01:39,432
and I believe he is the only one in this room

29
00:01:39,432 --> 00:01:43,436
who has witnessed that historic event 50 years ago.

30
00:01:45,872 --> 00:01:48,875
The creatives' vision was,

31
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:53,646
as articulated by Mac and Joe in the forward to the proceedings

32
00:01:53,646 --> 00:01:56,483
of that first conference.

33
00:01:56,483 --> 00:02:01,521
That vision was to provide an
opportunity for researchers

34
00:02:01,521 --> 00:02:03,556
to present their fresh new results

35
00:02:03,556 --> 00:02:06,392
in a dynamic growing field

36
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:10,663
and to bring researchers in
different disciplines together

37
00:02:10,663 --> 00:02:14,901
to cultivate cross-fertilization of ideas.

38
00:02:14,901 --> 00:02:18,037
And this was right on target.

39
00:02:18,037 --> 00:02:19,906
And this far-reaching vision

40
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:23,877
of its founders is still
the guiding light

41
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:27,814
at Allerton 50 years later.

42
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:32,519
It's-it's one of the longest running conferences

43
00:02:32,519 --> 00:02:36,923
at least that I'm aware
of in the systems area,

44
00:02:36,923 --> 00:02:39,125
and it's one
of the most prestigious.

45
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:44,197
It's perhaps the only longest
running conference

46
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,399
that has never changed
its venue.

47
00:02:46,399 --> 00:02:52,405
From the very beginning, it has been held at the Allerton House

48
00:02:52,405 --> 00:02:54,607
in Monticello, Illinois.

49
00:02:54,607 --> 00:02:58,578
Only a minor adjustment was made

50
00:02:58,578 --> 00:03:01,814
in going from the first to the second Allerton Conference

51
00:03:01,814 --> 00:03:03,983
in 1964,

52
00:03:03,983 --> 00:03:09,856
which was to move the date from the chilly mid November

53
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:14,627
to late September, which was September 28th through the 30th.

54
00:03:14,627 --> 00:03:18,665
That's when the-the second Allerton Conference was held,

55
00:03:18,665 --> 00:03:22,302
so that the attendees can enjoy the beautiful fall weather

56
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:24,604
at the Allerton grounds,

57
00:03:24,604 --> 00:03:27,574
and it looks like,
at least some of the days

58
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:32,645
we'll have that beautiful weather with us this year also.

59
00:03:32,645 --> 00:03:38,284
I'm told, eh, I'm not sure to what extent that it is a fact,

60
00:03:38,284 --> 00:03:46,225
but, eh, Mac actually wanted to hold the first, eh, conference

61
00:03:46,225 --> 00:03:49,629
in October,
the first week in October

62
00:03:49,629 --> 00:03:52,899
because that coincided,
would have coincided

63
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:58,037
with his birth date,
which was October 5th.

64
00:03:58,037 --> 00:04:01,374
But the Allerton House was not
available at the time,

65
00:04:01,374 --> 00:04:03,443
and I'm told
that was the reason why

66
00:04:03,443 --> 00:04:06,913
it was pushed to
November the 15th.

67
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:09,749
But then immediately
the following year,

68
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:12,986
it was brought back
to the first week

69
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:14,420
or the last week in September,

70
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:17,423
and since then
it has always been held

71
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,992
either the last week
in September

72
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:20,426
or the first week in October.

73
00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:24,864
The conference has evolved
over the years

74
00:04:24,864 --> 00:04:28,468
in parallel to the developments in the fields of communication,

75
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:29,769
control, and computing,

76
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:38,211
and in fact it has at times influenced, impacted, and shaped

77
00:04:38,211 --> 00:04:40,580
the evolutions in those fields.

78
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:43,383
Some of the very early results,

79
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:46,486
which then became landmarks
in these fields,

80
00:04:46,486 --> 00:04:49,856
were presented
at the Allerton Conference.

81
00:04:49,856 --> 00:04:52,191
To share with you some numbers,

82
00:04:52,191 --> 00:04:56,562
in 1963,
at the very first conference

83
00:04:56,562 --> 00:04:59,699
there were
11 technical sessions,

84
00:04:59,699 --> 00:05:03,436
3 general or what we now call plenary sessions,

85
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,438
they were not called
that way at the time,

86
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:13,312
with 62 individual presentations involving 84 authors.

87
00:05:13,312 --> 00:05:16,249
The proceedings of that
inaugural meeting

88
00:05:16,249 --> 00:05:23,122
was edited by Joe Cruz,
and it comprised 780 pages.

89
00:05:23,122 --> 00:05:28,194
And here I have actually a copy of that very first proceedings

90
00:05:28,194 --> 00:05:31,798
and it is in such good shape,
50 years later.

91
00:05:31,798 --> 00:05:32,799
[laughing]

92
00:05:32,799 --> 00:05:35,568
And the, and the proceedings in the intervening years

93
00:05:35,568 --> 00:05:37,503
have always looked like this.

94
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:39,038
Nothing has changed.

95
00:05:40,406 --> 00:05:45,344
And the, eh, today, as compared with those initial numbers,

96
00:05:45,344 --> 00:05:47,513
49 years later,

97
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:51,617
we have in the program
this week, 65 sessions,

98
00:05:51,617 --> 00:05:55,321
344 individual presentations,

99
00:05:55,321 --> 00:06:00,927
and have almost 500 authors, maybe even over 500 authors,

100
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:04,397
are involved in these papers which will be presented here.

101
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:07,300
So it's a, it's a major growth,

102
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:11,104
but we are limited by the size of the Allerton House,

103
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:13,873
so don't expect
those numbers to grow,

104
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:17,710
to double within the next even, uh, 10 years.

105
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:22,548
So talking about
the celebrations,

106
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:25,818
this, eh, golden anniversary of the Allerton Conference

107
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:30,990
is not the only important anniversary on our campus today.

108
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:35,128
Today is also the exact,
to the day,

109
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:38,998
first year anniversary of our chancellor, Phyllis Wise,

110
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:42,935
taking on the stewardship
of our campus.

111
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:47,273
We are delighted and honored
to have her here with us

112
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:51,144
this evening to share with us this important moment

113
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,346
and to officially open
this kick-off event

114
00:06:53,346 --> 00:06:55,648
for the golden anniversary.

115
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:58,151
Chancellor Wise also holds
the position

116
00:06:58,151 --> 00:07:00,386
of Vice President
of the University of Illinois,

117
00:07:00,386 --> 00:07:03,422
and as CEO of our campus

118
00:07:03,422 --> 00:07:06,592
she is responsible for all financial programs,

119
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:11,197
campus policies, and priorities with the mission of insuring

120
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:14,233
a transformative,
educational experience

121
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:17,837
for America's next generation
of leaders.

122
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:21,841
She has held, eh, faculty and
administrative appointments

123
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:23,910
at the University of Washington,

124
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:26,412
at the University
of California at Davis

125
00:07:26,412 --> 00:07:31,017
and Kentucky, eh, prior to joining here, eh, Illinois.

126
00:07:31,017 --> 00:07:33,519
Eh, her research career

127
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:36,756
has focused on issues
concerning women's health

128
00:07:36,756 --> 00:07:38,224
and gender based biology.

129
00:07:38,224 --> 00:07:41,093
She is a Fellow of AAAS

130
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:44,197
and a member of the
National Academy of Sciences

131
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:46,065
Institute of Medicine.

132
00:07:46,065 --> 00:07:48,100
Please join me in welcoming

133
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,269
Vice President and Chancellor, Phyllis Wise,

134
00:07:50,269 --> 00:07:56,275
to the podium, to open
this golden anniversary.

135
00:07:56,275 --> 00:08:02,949
[applause]

136
00:08:02,949 --> 00:08:04,217
(Phyllis Wise)
Somebody took good care

137
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:07,353
of these proceedings
from 50 years ago.

138
00:08:07,353 --> 00:08:10,923
It's a real honor to be here
in this overflowing room.

139
00:08:10,923 --> 00:08:13,292
I wonder whether
we're in fire code,

140
00:08:13,292 --> 00:08:14,427
but that's, that's okay.

141
00:08:14,427 --> 00:08:16,429
I won't say anything,
if you don't.

142
00:08:16,429 --> 00:08:19,632
Um, it is truly an honor
to be here

143
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:24,637
to, uh, welcome you to
the 50th anniversary celebration

144
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:27,306
of this wonderful conference with such a long

145
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:28,975
and strong history.

146
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:31,377
Y'know, um,
when I got this position

147
00:08:31,377 --> 00:08:34,647
I tried really hard to, uh,
do a lot of homework

148
00:08:34,647 --> 00:08:35,815
on the University of Illinois

149
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:38,317
to learn about
my new academic home,

150
00:08:38,317 --> 00:08:41,320
and I must admit I did not come across the Allerton Conference

151
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:44,824
so I must not have done
homework enough to realize

152
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:48,995
what a rich tradition was really started 50 years ago.

153
00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:52,164
Um, this conference
really is an illustration of,

154
00:08:52,164 --> 00:08:54,967
uh, what can happen
at a great university

155
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:57,670
with a 145 year history.

156
00:08:57,670 --> 00:09:02,608
Uh, the-the story that you just told, Professor Baser-Basar,

157
00:09:02,608 --> 00:09:06,279
and, uh, what I'm learning tonight about all of this,

158
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:08,147
is truly amazing.

159
00:09:08,147 --> 00:09:10,750
I think it's wonderful that it
started out at Allerton

160
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,752
and it continues
to be at Allerton.

161
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:14,086
I think it's wonderful to know

162
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:16,822
that sometimes traditions
should be carried on

163
00:09:16,822 --> 00:09:20,126
because they hav-are part of
the richness of the experience.

164
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:25,264
Um, you know, I-I just want to add tonight that, uh,

165
00:09:25,264 --> 00:09:29,101
I'm sure that this is the beginning of the next 50 years

166
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:30,102
of this conference,

167
00:09:30,102 --> 00:09:33,606
and though it won't get larger in terms of number,

168
00:09:33,606 --> 00:09:35,608
that that is actually
a good thing

169
00:09:35,608 --> 00:09:38,711
because sometimes the intimacy that you gather from having

170
00:09:38,711 --> 00:09:40,279
